1. UPPER BOUND AND LOWER BOUND 
UB - upper_bound(v.begin(),v.end(),value) - returns iterator to the first element equal or less than the given value
LB - lower_bound(v.begin(),v.end(),value) - returns iterator to the next greater element greater than the given value 
It works for sorted array 

2. BINARY SEARCH
binary_search(arr.begin(), arr.end(), value) - returns index

3. SORTING
sort(v.begin(), v.end()); - sorts the array 
sort(arr, arr + n); - does the same

4. CONVERTING STRING TO INT 
stoi(string) returns int value;

5. CONVERTING INT TO STRING
to_string(num) returns string;

6. NUMBER OF DIGITS IN NUM USING LOG
int cnt = (int)(log10(n)+1);

7. MINIMUM ELEMENT / MAX ELEMENT in vector
min_element(v.begin(),v.end()); - returns iterator;
max_element(v.begin(),v.end()); - returns iterator;

8. SUM OF VECTOR 
accumulate(v.begin(),v.end(),0);
find and count also reverse (reverse also works in strings)




